OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FA retired IT analyst has become the
OL,7,Fseventh person to win the #1 million
OL,8,Fjackpot on Who Wants To Be A
OL,9,FMillionaire?
OL,11,FRoman Dubowski said winning the ITV
OL,12,Fgame show, which is hosted by Jeremy
OL,13,FClarkson, was "unreal", adding that he
OL,14,F"had to have a cup of tea" afterwards.
OL,16,FThe contestant is planning on buying a
OL,17,Fnew house with his prize money and
OL,18,Falso hopes to travel and visit
OL,19,Fdestinations including New Zealand and
OL,20,FSouth America.
OL,26,@uD@OOUuD@VO]vD@AOUvD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FRoman, who does quizzing as a hobby,
OL,7,Fcorrectly answered the final 15th
OL,8,Fquestion, which was: "Used since 1876,
OL,9,Fwhich trademarked logo is described in
OL,10,Fthe James Joyce novel Ulysses and
OL,11,Fdepicted in works by Manet and
OL,12,FPicasso?"
OL,14,FThe options were Bass Ale, The Famous
OL,15,FGrouse, Coca-Cola and Stella Artois.
OL,17,FDescribing the final question, Roman
OL,18,Fsaid: "When it came up... I thought, I
OL,19,Fthink I know this straight away."
OL,26,@pD@VOUtD@IO]zD@GOU{D@aO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FHe explained that he had seen the
OL,7,FManet painting ` called A Bar at the
OL,8,FFolies-Bergere ` at The Courtauld
OL,9,FGallery in London.
OL,11,FHe said he could "distinctly" remember
OL,12,Fseeing a red triangle on the painting,
OL,13,Fwhich "has always been the symbol of
OL,14,FBass beer".
OL,16,FThe contestant decided to use the 50/
OL,17,F50 lifeline to answer the question and
OL,18,Fsaid that when the answers were
OL,19,Fnarrowed down to Coca-Cola and Bass
OL,20,FAle, he thought "well I may as well go
OL,21,Ffor it".
OL,26,@sD@ROUsD@]O]uD@GOUvD@JO]|D@QOU}D@GO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FRoman, who is originally from
OL,7,FManchester but now lives just outside
OL,8,FStockport, correctly answered Bass Ale.
OL,10,FHe said that Clarkson, 66, had given
OL,11,Fhim some "very good" advice about
OL,12,Fusing the 50/50 lifeline which had
OL,13,F"stayed with me throughout the show".
OL,15,FAccording to Mr Dubowski, Clarkson
OL,16,Ftold him that the lifeline should be
OL,17,Fused when you have got an "inkling"
OL,18,Fthat one or two of the answers are
OL,19,Fcorrect.
OL,26,@sD@JOUsD@TO]uD@AOUuD@dO]yD@[OUyD@cO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FAsked to describe how he felt when he
OL,7,Fanswered that final question
OL,8,Fcorrectly, he said: "It felt unreal...
OL,9,Fit didn't feel like the real world,
OL,10,Falmost, this isn't where I expected to
OL,11,Fbe. It didn't sink in until later."
OL,13,FDuring the show, Mr Dubowski
OL,14,Fexperienced a "strange bit of self-
OL,15,Fdoubt" after he was asked what is
OL,16,Fmixed with vinegar, mustard and oil to
OL,17,Fmake a basic mayonnaise.
OL,19,FThe possible answers were plain flour,
OL,20,Fsalted butter, egg yolk and double
OL,21,Fcream.
OL,26,@pD@UOUsD@cO]vD@OOUwD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FMr Dubowski said that cooking is one
OL,7,Fof his "weaker points" and he made the
OL,8,Fdecision to use the ask the audience
OL,9,Flifeline for help answering, with 93%
OL,10,Fopting for the correct answer ` egg
OL,11,Fyolk.
OL,13,FThe contestant said that in that
OL,14,Fmoment he thought he "might go and
OL,15,Fwalk away with nothing".
OL,17,FMr Dubowski said: "That was like, you
OL,18,Fknow, shame and humiliation almost, so
OL,19,FI had to put it to the audience."
OL,26,@oD@HOUoD@VO]vD@VOUwD@WO]yD@SOU{D@aO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FAsked what he did after the show
OL,7,Fended, he said: "I did sort of go home
OL,8,Fquietly, to be honest, I didn't get
OL,9,Fdrunk ` I had to have a cup of tea.
OL,11,F"I think it was just sitting in a
OL,12,Fquiet room and letting it all sink in,
OL,13,Fand thinking about what happened in
OL,14,Fthe previous 24 hours."
OL,16,FMr Dubowski said the first person he
OL,17,Ftold about the win was his sister,
OL,18,Fadding that she was "absolutely
OL,19,Fthrilled" for him.
OL,26,@oD@QOUsD@AOUvD@WO]zD@UOU{D@IO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,FHe said he will be giving some of his
OL,7,Fprize money to his niece and nephew.
OL,9,FMr Dubowski said he had "always"
OL,10,Fwanted to appear on the game show and
OL,11,Fhad even applied to it when Chris
OL,12,FTarrant was the host ` but said he
OL,13,F"didn't get a response".
OL,15,FThe retired IT worker also applied
OL,16,Fafter lockdown, but was not successful.
OL,18,FHe added: "Then in October last year,
OL,19,FI suddenly saw an advertisement, or
OL,20,Fsomething online saying they're
OL,21,Frecruiting for new competitors again.
OL,26,@qD@YOUqD@`O]uD@AOUuD@WO]zD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,399,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F398A1777359931
OL,3,CQuizzer 'had to have cuppa' after
OL,4,Cwinning Who Wants To Be A Millionaire?
OL,6,F"I thought oh, might as well try
OL,7,Fagain, got nothing to lose, and just
OL,8,Ffrom that sort of casual opening, it
OL,9,Fended up with the top prize.
OL,11,F"So (I'm) just happy I did it really."
OL,13,FAsked what advice he has for other
OL,14,Fquizzers, Mr Dubowski recommended they
OL,15,Fread a book called A To Z Of
OL,16,FEverything by Trevor Montague.
OL,18,FPrior to Mr Dubowski's win, only six
OL,19,Fcontestants in the UK's version of the
OL,20,Fshow had won the #1 million prize.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUsD@fO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G9/10
